<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-C21DAA9F-FFD5-4B78-80E0-B76A3FCF9528" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-C21DAA9F-FFD5-4B78-80E0-B76A3FCF9528" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Troubleshoot ORS connection issues</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M148684-B19"><p class="- topic/p ">What can you do if <ph class="- topic/ph " translate="no">On Remote Service</ph> does not work ? 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When “On Remote Service ” is configured correctly on a system, the system will sent a heartbeat signal to the Backoffice every 30 seconds. If the system is not known in “Prisma Service” or no heartbeats are received recently, the system might be configured incorrectly or local network settings have been changed 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="M148684-B20" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Troubleshoot procedure</title><p class="- topic/p ">To troubleshoot the connection issues we will follow the below steps to find the root cause 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Check connection Status and setting. 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Check SOID 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Check if ORS is enabled 
</p></li></ul></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Check Proxy settings 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Customer firewall requirements 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> URL Whitelisting for outbound connection 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Port usage (outbound) 
</p></li></ul></li></ol></section><section id="GUID-FBDE3079-8988-4F6F-A7BC-E2914D2FD4FC" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">1 Check connection Status and Setting</title><p class="- topic/p ">You can check the status and the settings via the UI. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When the SOID has not been configured correctly during installation, the systems will not be visible within Prisma Service for your service organization. 
</p><table id="GUID-3553B4FF-6F19-498D-A707-9F03438F1C24" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Find your SOID 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If you don’t know you Service Organization ID applicable to your region/country, please check document: 
<xref keyref="FAQDOIS001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-611135E7-18E3-4468-8484-4FA6FE396EBE.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text What to do when you do not know the SOID?>What to do when you do not know the SOID</xref> . 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap the System icon. 
</p><fig id="GUID-0490CD29-62A5-437B-9424-A4998C858E38" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-713ACEFA-3423-4929-92E3-D10312746446-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-713ACEFA-3423-4929-92E3-D10312746446-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Remote services. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Login as administrator (71617000). 
</p><fig id="GUID-BD8409E9-6145-482B-862E-98216B80B23A" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-2F6AC1DD-856C-491A-80A8-E52DE7B5C2A4-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2F6AC1DD-856C-491A-80A8-E52DE7B5C2A4-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Remote connection. 
</p><fig id="GUID-9E59527F-9B36-4A54-80CE-FA1C5277FC28" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-93C34C30-FA6A-46DA-8419-AB64B5119E0F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-93C34C30-FA6A-46DA-8419-AB64B5119E0F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check the Service Organization ID applicable for your region/country. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Correct it if necessary! 
</p><fig id="GUID-B27B2C5D-DF28-4812-A8B1-4A8295781162" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-B4FB3AF2-5E51-4896-8ED1-5F2870B38298-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B4FB3AF2-5E51-4896-8ED1-5F2870B38298-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Enable Remote connection!! 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Save. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click on ‘’Test remote connection” 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check the Remote connection status is 'Connected'. 
</p><fig id="GUID-E69E06AC-F96D-4941-9322-B08B7EFB5A42" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-227CD82B-E0C4-46C3-B52D-B05CD490BDB1-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-227CD82B-E0C4-46C3-B52D-B05CD490BDB1-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Use PRISMAservice to connect to the ORS server: 
<xref href="https://prismaservice.cpp.canon/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://prismaservice.cpp.canon/</xref>. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Search for the <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph> configuration. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case the “Remote connection test” returns a failure message, continue with next chapter: “Check Proxy settings” 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-1D9DBC56-90EB-40EB-938B-5ADA943804AF" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">2 Check Proxy settings</title><p class="- topic/p ">When proxy settings have been changed or when set incorrectly, connection to the ORS server is not possible. 
</p><table id="GUID-504AA5CA-FB6C-4054-8E11-78D826D6926B" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ask the local administrator for the correct proxy settings: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Proxy Server name 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Proxy server port 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Proxy servicer domain 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Proxy authentication required&gt; 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Proxy authentication type 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Proxy User name for authentication 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Proxy Password for authentication 
</p></li></ul></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap the System icon. 
</p><fig id="GUID-0EBDF5FC-1B51-4F69-B5C5-247CD8A99052" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-713ACEFA-3423-4929-92E3-D10312746446-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-713ACEFA-3423-4929-92E3-D10312746446-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Remote services. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Login as administrator (71617000). 
</p><fig id="GUID-93E13D40-BF0F-4ACF-A369-6FEA4311E1C1" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-2F6AC1DD-856C-491A-80A8-E52DE7B5C2A4-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2F6AC1DD-856C-491A-80A8-E52DE7B5C2A4-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Proxy settings. 
</p><fig id="GUID-2201F369-B362-4963-81CE-643B3ECBA315" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-170A9E06-4E6F-4F28-B95E-F83479C4D056-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-170A9E06-4E6F-4F28-B95E-F83479C4D056-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Enter all required Proxy settings for this customer (the values shown are just examples). 
</p><fig id="GUID-EF9F76DA-CDAF-441B-9EF9-D811CA800777" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-0419C532-DBDE-4D02-84E2-FE5AA1A5C399-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0419C532-DBDE-4D02-84E2-FE5AA1A5C399-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Save. 
</p><fig id="GUID-591136F3-CD7F-4772-90A1-E35F45401B47" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-4EF3B3C4-44A7-4113-A3C8-18913E5647CF-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4EF3B3C4-44A7-4113-A3C8-18913E5647CF-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tap Remote connection and check Connection Status is 'Connected'. 
</p><fig id="GUID-064B3101-AA33-40E3-B969-BD81722F09D4" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-227CD82B-E0C4-46C3-B52D-B05CD490BDB1-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-227CD82B-E0C4-46C3-B52D-B05CD490BDB1-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Use PRISMAservice to connect to the ORS server: 
<xref href="https://prismaservice.cpp.canon/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://prismaservice.cpp.canon/</xref>. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Search for the <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph>Colorado 1650 configuration. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In case the “Remote connection test” returns a failure message, continue with next chapter: “Check Proxy settings” 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-D752FF77-ECD1-4D88-B1AA-87A89B427512" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">3 Check Customer firewall requirements</title><p class="- topic/p ">Depending on the customer internet access policy it might be needed to white list several URLs for outbound communication on the customer Firewall / Proxy Server. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the URL or the communication port is blocked, one or more remote functionality might not work. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Below is an overview of the functionality and URL/port used for communication. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Please check with the customer administrator if white listing is needed. 
</p><note id="GUID-3A6A4DAA-E98D-4866-985A-24366055AF13" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">On Prisma Service there is an ORS whitepaper available with detailed information for the customer. 
</p></note><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref keyref="Proxy_and_Firewal_requirements" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-6AA16343-FD4F-4A39-9CA0-5ED532F3AE65.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Proxy and Firewall requirements?>Proxy and Firewall requirements</xref> for detailed information on URLs and Port usage. 
</p></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-DFD95E44-6FE2-4690-855D-446A64ABF90C.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>ORS: On Remote Service</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</concept>